&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;CallRail is looking for a Content Marketing Manager.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;The Content Marketing Manager will develop and execute copy and content strategies that drive engagement at all stages of buyer and customer journeys.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In conjunction with the rest of the content and SEO team, the Content Marketing Manager focuses on ideating and writing content - from case studies to blog posts, and ebooks - designed to help CallRail prospects and customers grow in marketing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Content Marketing Manager will constantly seek to create and align content marketing strategy to a growing understanding of who CallRail customers and leads are, what pain points they bring into a buying decision, and what stages exist in their particular journey toward conversion - then proposing, writing and/or editing content to this end.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Efficiently guide and/or create content in accordance with CallRail content strategy - partnering with internal and external contributors to ensure timely publishing of high-quality, helpful, rich content.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI tools to improve content research, ideation, drafting, and optimization, while maintaining editorial quality and strategic oversight.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pay close attention to pre-determined success metrics for content strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously learn about the CallRail platform, products, and AI capabilities to build a foundational understanding of how they work together and what problems they solve. Seek out internal subject matter experts to strengthen this perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with content team members to create and execute CallRail’s content strategy for ensuring engaging content is created for all buyer and customer personas in defined markets at every stage of the buyer’s journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with stakeholders across marketing and other departments to identify content opportunities, determine ideal formats, and align content initiatives with larger business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and manage third-party resources as required, including agencies, writers, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on industry trends, SEO developments, AI advancements, and content marketing best practices to help CallRail remain competitive and innovative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion experimentation with new content formats, AI-driven discovery channels, and evolving search behaviors to expand reach and improve performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in content marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent writing, editing, and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong editorial governance and grasp of modern, web-driven English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and self-motivated with a high level of initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent time management and project management skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing and editing a large volume of content across formats and channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using AI tools to improve content research, creation, or workflow efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to efficiently research content topics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creativity in ideating content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundational SEO knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in SaaS preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to measure and monitor the results of initiatives and programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Public Relation

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;CallRail is looking for a Design Systems Designer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re looking for a Product Designer to support the growth and adoption of our design system across&lt;br&gt;web and mobile. This role focuses on building, maintaining, and documenting components, while&lt;br&gt;helping ensure consistent usage across the product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work closely with the design systems workstream and cross-functional partners to translate&lt;br&gt;system standards into scalable, usable outputs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Component development &amp;amp; maintenance&lt;br&gt;● Build and maintain Figma components using established design system standards&lt;br&gt;● Ensure components include complete variants, states, and properties&lt;br&gt;● Apply tokens consistently across components&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Documentation &amp;amp; guidance&lt;br&gt;● Translate design system decisions into clear, usable documentation&lt;br&gt;● Create lightweight references for component anatomy, states, and behaviors&lt;br&gt;● Support token-to-component mapping for improved clarity and reuse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design QA &amp;amp; support&lt;br&gt;● Review product designs for alignment with design system standards&lt;br&gt;● Identify inconsistencies and recommend system-aligned solutions&lt;br&gt;● Partner with designers to support implementation and iteration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Audit &amp;amp; migration support&lt;br&gt;● Audit product UI to identify opportunities for standardization&lt;br&gt;● Support migration from legacy patterns to design system components&lt;br&gt;● Help consolidate redundant or inconsistent patterns&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI prototyping workflows&lt;br&gt;● Prepare inputs (screenshots, annotations, context) for AI-generated prototypes&lt;br&gt;● Assist in refining outputs to align with design system standards&lt;br&gt;● Support development of repeatable workflows for scalable prototyping&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core skills &amp;amp; mindset&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Strong experience building and maintaining components in Figma (variants, properties, auto&lt;br&gt;layout)&lt;br&gt;● High attention to detail and consistency in visual and interaction design&lt;br&gt;● Comfortable working within established systems and applying standards accurately&lt;br&gt;● Ability to take defined patterns and execute them cleanly and thoroughly&lt;br&gt;● Collaborative and responsive when working with designers and engineers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● ~2–5 years of experience in product design or a related field (or equivalent hands-on&lt;br&gt;experience)&lt;br&gt;● Experience working with component-based design systems or design libraries&lt;br&gt;● Familiarity with developer handoff or front-end constraints&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Exposure to token-based design systems&lt;br&gt;● Interest in improving workflows and scaling design system adoption&lt;br&gt;● Curiosity about AI-assisted design or prototyping workflows&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How you’ll work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Partner closely with the design systems workstream to support system adoption&lt;br&gt;● Collaborate with product designers and engineers to ensure consistency&lt;br&gt;● Contribute to a system that supports both current product needs and future evolution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;If you do not meet all the requirements listed, we still encourage you to apply! No job description is perfect, and we may also have another opportunity that aligns with your skills and experience.&lt;/em&gt;&lt

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CallRail is seeking an Inside Sales Representative (ISR) to join our high-performing Small Business (SMB) sales team. As a key driver of growth, you&#39;ll help small businesses discover how CallRail&#39;s solutions can support their success while contributing to the continued expansion of our customer base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll engage exclusively with warm inbound leads—SMB prospects who have expressed interest in CallRail or started a free trial. Rather than cold calling, you&#39;ll focus on conducting consultative product demonstrations, identifying customer challenges and goals, and showcasing the value of CallRail&#39;s suite of solutions. Your success will come from building strong relationships, delivering a seamless buying experience, and converting interested prospects into long-term customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will conduct product demos for SMB prospects and convert them to free trials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement net new leads with CallRail’s suite of products and convert them to customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uncover business initiatives and pain points to map back to our solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and understand various lines of business and personas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sell on Value and Return on Investment vs. technical functionality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of exceeding quota as an Account Executive or SDR&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 year of software sales experience as an Account Executive or SDR; strong preference for marketing technology sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with high volume SMB sales is a huge plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Amazing written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in solution-selling, account planning, and forecasting/pipeline management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Outreach is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency using Salesforce.com and Google Suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can work as part of a team and/or independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knows how to navigate a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;If you do not meet all the requirements listed, we still encourage you to apply! No job description is perfect, and we may also have another opportunity that aligns with your skills and experience.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Perks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Healthcare (one option covered at 100% for employees), Dental &amp;amp; Vision Coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive HSA with company matching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid parental leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible vacation policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K options with company dollar-for-dollar match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee stock options available from day one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$2,000 annual educational allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Catered lunch every Tuesday * an in-office perk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MARTA transportation or office parking expenses covered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee charitable donation company match, up to $500 annually&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular company outings and events&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid work options with $500 office stipend to set up your home office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designated bike storage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
