&lt;li&gt;Clearly define and articulate customer problems, gaps, and opportunities that will deliver the most value to the customers and the viability for the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay on top of AI/ML market trends and competitive landscape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a great partner to engineers and designers in discovering the best solutions to those problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own your roadmap and its execution, including responsibilities like defining features, writing acceptance criteria and user stories, refining wireframes and prototypes, test plans, and release checklists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate functionality and release plans internally to the stakeholders across the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize product development work for your team and manage the backlog of features based on company priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and track measures of success for your domain and report regularly on findings, learnings, and next steps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the daily workflow with a sprint team of engineers, QA, and designers. Do whatever your team needs to help them keep moving.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
